1. Preface

This document intends to provide brief PlantUML example to show what the ability of PlantUml. For complete PlantUML information, check the PlantUML_Language_Reference_Guide_ZH.pdf.

http://plantuml.com provides more.

This document is hosted at http://gitlab.china.nsn-net.net/devhz2/techdoc/ . You are free to edit it for comments/information.

3.2. Editor

There are a lot of ways to edit PlantUML. The simplest is normal Text edit. http://plantuml.com/running lists a lot of options. Here are some of them:

  • Confluence

  • Word

  • Eclipse

  • Emacs

  • Sublime

  • Pandoc

  • Visual Studio Code + Plugin (jebbs.plantuml)

Software installation URL

3.2.1. Visual Studio Code

Visual Studio Code is a lightweight editor for text editing, developed by Microsoft.

Installation

  1. Download it from

    https://code.visualstudio.com/download

  2. Install

  3. Install Plugin

  4. Optional: install graphviz

  5. Optional: install jlatexmath

    If Math capability is required, unzip plantuml-jlatexmath.zip into C:\Users\USERNAME\.vscode\extensions\jebbs.plantuml-1.8.1

Usage

  1. Create one plantuml file

  2. Activate PlantUML preview

    View ▸ Command Palette ▸ PlantUML: Preview Current Diagram

Sequence Example

3.2.2. Intellij IDEA Community

IDEA is another free editor for PlantUML.

Installation

  1. Download

    https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/download/#section=windows

  2. Install

  3. Optional: Config Proxy

    If no direct connection to plugin server, set proper proxy

  4. Install plugin

    Files ▸ Settings ▸ Plugins

Usage

  1. Create one project (whatever it is)

  2. Create one plantuml file

    The plugin will be activated automatically.

  3. Here is one example

4. Run from command line

4.1. Edit Source file

Edit one file contains plantuml commands, e.g. simple.plantuml

@startuml
Alice -> Bob: test
@enduml

4.2. Run

java -jar plantuml.jar simple.plantuml

One png file will be generated.

There are many way to run plantuml, check http://plantuml.com/running to find out more.

5. UML Diagrams

5.1. Sequence Diagram

There are some different type of Participant: participant, actor, boundary, control, entity, database

 
@startuml

box "Social Senario" #LightBlue
	actor Bob
	actor Alice
end box

entity CoreSche as Handler
control "Core Cell" as Server
participant DbProxy
database DB

== Conversation ==

autonumber "<b>[000]"
Bob -> Alice : one interesting website
Bob <- Alice : ???

autonumber 15 "<b>(<u>##</u>)"
Bob -> Alice : Here is the link, try it.
Bob <- Alice : Sure.

...5 Days latter...

== Register ==

rnote over Server
 "r" as rectangle
 "h" as hexagon
endrnote

autonumber 10 10 "<font color=red><b>TTI 0  "

Alice -> Server: Register
Server -> Handler : Regist(Alice)
activate Handler

Handler -> DbProxy: << createUser(Alice) >>
activate DbProxy

DbProxy -> DB: store(Alice)
activate DB
DB --> DbProxy: WorkDone
destroy DB

DbProxy --> Handler : Stored
destroy DbProxy

Handler --> Server: RequestCreated
deactivate Handler

Server -> Alice: Done
deactivate Server

@enduml

5.2. Usecase Diagram

@startuml
:Main Admin: as Admin
(Use the application) as (Use)

User -> (Start)
User --> (Use)

Admin ---> (Use)

note right of Admin : This is an example.

note right of (Use)
  A note can also
  be on several lines
end note

note "This note is connected\nto several objects." as N2
(Start) .. N2
N2 .. (Use)
@enduml

5.3. Class Diagram

@startuml

class Car {
.. private ..
 -field1
.. protected ..
 #field2
.. package private ..
 ~method1()
.. public ..
 +method2()
}

class Wheel {
  You can use
  several lines
  ..
  as you want
  and group
  ==
  things together.
  __
  You can have as many groups
  as you want
  --
  End of class
}

class Driver {
  .. Simple Getter ..
  + getName()
  + getAddress()
  .. Some setter ..
  + setName()
  __ private data __
  int age
  -- encrypted --
  String password
}

class Car

Driver - Car : drives >
Car *- Wheel : have 4 >
Car -- Person : < owns

@enduml

5.4. Activity Diagram

@startuml
|User|
start
|#AntiqueWhite|Service|
    :wait for user interaction;
|User|
partition Arrows {
if (test) then
  -[#blue]->
  :Action 1012;
  -[#green,dashed]-> The text can
  also be on several lines
  and **very** long...;
  :Action 2;
else
  -[#black,dotted]->
  :No Action;
-> You can put text on arrows;
endif
-[#gray,bold]->
}
|Service|
:Handle Another User;
stop
@enduml

5.5. Component Diagram

@startuml

package "Some Group" {
  HTTP - [First Component]
  [Another Component]
}

node "Other Groups" {
  FTP - [Second Component]
  [First Component] --> FTP
}

cloud {
  [Example 1]
}


database "MySql" {
  folder "This is my folder" {
    [Folder 3]
  }
  frame "Foo" {
    [Frame 4]
  }
}


[Another Component] --> [Example 1]
[Example 1] --> [Folder 3]
[Folder 3] --> [Frame 4]

@enduml

5.6. State Diagram

@startuml

scale 600 width

[*] -> State1
State1 --> State2 : Succeeded
State1 --> [*] : Aborted
State2 --> State3 : Succeeded
State2 --> [*] : Aborted
state State3 {
  state "Accumulate Enough Data\nLong State Name" as long1
  long1 : Just a test
  [*] --> long1
  long1 --> long1 : New Data
  long1 --> ProcessData : Enough Data
}
State3 --> State3 : Failed
State3 --> [*] : Succeeded / Save Result
State3 --> [*] : Aborted

@enduml

abstract class Person {

    -String name
    +String getName

    + study()

Teacher "*" .. "*" Student : association

Department o-- Teacher : aggregation

 has-a .

end note

Teacher -- Question : create >

Question <|-- HealthyQuestion
@enduml

5.8. Deployment Diagram

@startuml

skinparam rectangle {
    roundCorner<<Concept>> 25
}

frame elements {
actor actor
agent agent
artifact artifact
boundary boundary
card card
cloud cloud
component component
control control
database database
entity entity
file file
folder folder
frame frame
interface  interface
node node
package package
queue queue

rectangle rectangle
storage storage
usecase usecase
}

rectangle Nodes <<Concept>> {
node node1
node node2
node node3
node node4
node node5
node1 -- node2
node1 .. node3
node4 ~~ node1
node5 == node1
}

artifact ArtifactExample {
artifact artifact1
artifact artifact2
artifact artifact3
artifact artifact4
artifact artifact5
artifact artifact6
artifact artifact7
artifact artifact8
artifact artifact9
artifact artifact10
artifact1 --> artifact2
artifact1 --* artifact3
artifact1 --o artifact4
artifact5 --+ artifact1
artifact6 --# artifact1
artifact7 -->> artifact1
artifact8 -right-0 artifact1
artifact1 -right-^ artifact9
artifact1 --(0 artifact10
}

cloud CloudExample {
cloud cloud1
cloud cloud2
cloud cloud3
cloud cloud4
cloud cloud5
cloud1 -0- cloud2
cloud3 -0)- cloud1
cloud4 -(0- cloud1
cloud1 -(0)- cloud5
}

CloudExample -right-> ArtifactExample
elements -down-# CloudExample
Nodes -left-o elements
ArtifactExample -up-* Nodes

@enduml

5.9. Timing Diagram

@startuml

concise "UE" as ue
concise "MAC PS" as ps
concise "L2" as l2

@ue
0 is Idle
+80 is Raching
ue -> ps : PHY_RACH_xxxx

@ps
0 is working


@l2
0 is " "
+20 is " "
l2 -> ps : PS_ADDRESS_CONFIG_xxxx
+180 is "Stoping UE"
l2 -> ps : PS_STOP_UE_xxxx

@enduml

6. Non-UML Diagram

6.1. Gantt Diagram

@startuml
Project starts the 30th of June 2017
[Preparation] as [pre] lasts 4 days
[Sequence Diagram] as [seq] lasts 4 days
[Math Diagram] as [math] lasts 3 days
[Timing Diagram] as [timing] lasts 2 days
[Gantt Diagram] as [gantt] lasts 5 days
[Combine PPT] as [ppt] lasts 2 days
[Book Meeting Room] as [book] lasts 1 days
[Use Case Diagram] as [use] lasts 3 days
[Activity Diagram] as [activity] lasts 4 days
[State Diagram] as [state] lasts 4 days
[Store jar files] as [jars] lasts 1 days
[Editor Introduction] as [editor] lasts 7 days

[seq] starts at [pre]'s end
[math] starts at [seq]'s end
[jars] starts at [pre]'s end
[gantt] starts at [math]'s end
[ppt] starts at [gantt]'s end
[book] starts at [ppt]'s end
[timing] starts at [math]'s end
[use] starts at [seq]'s end
[activity] starts at [use]'s end
[state] starts at [pre]'s end
[editor] starts at [pre]'s end

@enduml

6.2. Math Diagram

@startuml

Bob -> Alice : Can you solve: :<math>int_0^1f(x)dx</math>;
Alice --> Bob: <math>x = (-b+-sqrt(b^2-4ac))/(2a)</math>
note right
Unzip plantuml-jlatexmath.zip to
C:\Users\USERNAME\.vscode\extensions\jebbs.plantuml-1.8.1
C:\Users\USERNAME\.IdeaIC2017.1\config\plugins\plantuml4idea\lib

<math>d/dxf(x)=lim_(h->0)(f(x+h)-f(x))/h</math>
<latex>P(y|\mathbf{x}) \mbox{ or } f(\mathbf{x})+\epsilon</latex>
end note
@enduml

6.3. Ditaa Diagram

@startuml
ditaa(--no-shadows, scale=1.2)
/--------\   +-------+
|cAAA    +---+Version|
|  Data  |   |   V3  |
|  Base  |   |cRED{d}|
|     {s}|   +-------+
\---+----/

+--+
|  |
+--+

+--------+   +-------+    +-------+
|        +---+ ditaa +--> |       |
|  Text  |   +-------+    |diagram|
|Document|   |!magic!|    |       |
|     {d}|   |       |    |       |
+---+----+   +-------+    +-------+
    :                         ^
    |       Lots of work      |
    +-------------------------+

@enduml

6.4. Dot Diagram

@startdot
digraph foo {
  node [style=rounded]
  node1 [shape=box]
  node2 [fillcolor=yellow, style="rounded,filled", shape=diamond]
  node3 [shape=record, label="{ a | b | c }"]

  node1 -> node2 -> node3
}
@enddot
